Airport closure to international flights
The Cheddi Jagan International Airport at Timehri and the Eugene Correia Airport at Ogle are closed to all international flights from 17 March 2020. The closure is scheduled to last for 14 days.
Borders
On 19 March the Government of Brazil announced that it was closing its borders for 15 days with neighbouring countries, including Guyana. This measure will be applied to foreigners wishing to enter Brazil, it does not apply to Brazilians wishing to return to the country.
Further information
See additional advice on making travel plans to return to the UK, or what to do if you cannot depart immediately.
